1	Use Case [#1]:  [Register User Account]

1.1	Description
The Customer decides to register a user account before purchasing a specific service from the online catalog for delivery.

1.2	Level
High Level

1.3	Trigger
The Customer clicks sign up link.

1.4	Primary Actor
Customer

1.5	Additional/Supporting Actors

1.6	Stakeholders 
Stakeholders:
•	Business admin

1.7	Preconditions
The Customer must have an active internet connection, logged onto application.

1.8	Main Success Scenario
1.	Customer chooses to sign up to be able to make a booking request.
2.	Customers enters fullname, email, phone number, address and password.
3.	Customer selects their gender and age range.
4.	Application saves details and sends the log-in details via email
5.	Customer is redirected to log-in screen


1.9	Extensions
1.	Exception: Details are missing/incorrect:
1.	Application displays warnings
2.	The customer re-enters correct information.
3.	Application proceeds with the process.

1.10	Post Conditions
1.10.1	Success End Condition
The customer receives a registration confirmation.
 
1.10.2	Minimal Guarantees
1.10.3	Failure End Condition
The customer fails to register an account and cannot make booking requests.

1.11	Frequency
Always

1.12	Special Requirements
1.12.1	Performance
The customer should be able to complete registration within 3 minutes

1.12.2	Security
Customer’s password will be masked in the display and in th email confirmation.
 
1.12.3	Usability / Accessibility
Customer must be able to view page in English.

1.12.4	Other

1.13	Issues and Next Steps
Address has to be a multiline input with city, suburb, street, house/complex no. and postal code
Phone number must be nine digits with the country code already inputed for them
